Note on regulatory content: The reference files in this skill contain
original analytical summaries of Canadian regulatory publications. The
underlying publications themselves (OSFI guidelines, provincial regulations,
federal and provincial statutes) are the property of their respective
issuers. Where those issuers are the Government of Canada or a provincial
Crown, Crown copyright applies to the underlying publications, and this
skill's license covers only the analytical summary, structure, and
organization — not the underlying regulatory text. Users who need verbatim
regulator text should retrieve it directly from the regulator's website.
